UID:JO-FKajhEMNn7xOiT_Q9x
SUMMARY:Distinguished Lecture with Ken Goldberg
DTSTAMP:20260630T134500Z
DTSTART:20260924T210000Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP to Attend (https://k2i.wufoo.com/forms/distinguished-lectu
	re-with-ken-goldberg/): The distinguished lecture is from 4:00-5:00 PM\, f
	ollowed by a social from 5:00-6:00 PMSpeaker: Ken Goldberg\, PhD (https://
	goldberg.berkeley.edu/) — William S. Floyd Distinguished Professor of Engi
	neering at UC Berkeley and President of the Robot Learning Foundation  Tal
	k Title: TBD  When: Thursday\, September 24\, 2026 @ 4:00-6:00 PM Central 
	 Where: Auditorium\, Duncan Hall\, Rice University (6100 Main St.\, Housto
	n\, TX 77005)  Parking: Paid parking will be available in Founder's Court 
	Lot or the Entrance 3 (COB) Garage. Visit the Rice University Campus Maps 
	webpage (https://www.rice.edu/campus-maps) for directions.  Organizers: Ke
	n Kennedy Institute (https://kenkennedy.rice.edu/)Speaker Bio        Ken G
	oldberg is William S. Floyd Distinguished Professor of Engineering at UC B
	erkeley\, President of the international Robot Learning Foundation\, IEEE 
	Fellow\, co-founder and Editor-in-Chief emeritus of the IEEE Transactions 
	on Automation Science and Engineering (T-ASE)\, and Co-Founder/Chief Scien
	tist of Ambi Robotics. Ken leads research in robotics and automation: gras
	ping\, manipulation\, and learning for applications in warehouses\, homes\
	, agriculture\, and robot-assisted surgery. He is Distinguished Professor 
	of IEOR\, EECS\, and Art Practice. Ken has published 12 US patents and ove
	r 450 refereed papers. He has presented over 600 invited lectures to acade
	mic and corporate audiences.\n\nhttps://events.rice.edu/live/events/distin
	guished-lecture-with-ken-goldberg\n\nFrom Rice University - Open to the Pu
	blic
URL:https://events.rice.edu/live/events/distinguished-lecture-with-ken-gold
	berg
GEO:29.7174;-95.4018
LOCATION:Duncan Hall
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:rice-public-events
CATEGORIES:Rice University - Open to the Public
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
